{"id":"arm","term":"Arm","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Used to denote power (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 10:15\">Ps. 10:15</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezekiel 30:21\">Ezek. 30:21</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 48:25\">Jer. 48:25</a>). It is also used of the omnipotence of God (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 15:16\">Ex. 15:16</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 89:13\">Ps. 89:13</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 98:1\">98:1</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 77:15\">77:15</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 53:1\">Isa. 53:1</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"John 12:38\">John 12:38</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 13:17\">Acts 13:17</a>)</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Psalms 10:15","Ezekiel 30:21","Jeremiah 48:25","Exodus 15:16","Psalms 89:13","Psalms 98:1","Psalms 77:15","Isaiah 53:1","John 12:38","Acts 13:17"]}